learning_outcomes.en:
Students will be able to: 
1) identify and analyse the signifying, symbolic and ideological systems;
2) understand the role of communication in establishing social relations;
3) define semiotic aspects of sociopolitical research and describe relations between these;
4) define the major paradigms, theories, and concepts in 20th century theoretical approaches of power ;
5) apply critical reading and analytical skills to various academic and non-academic texts;
6) express personal theoretical preferences and defend them by constructing evidence-based arguments.
7) develop the skills of team work
